---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'axa-global', text: 'AXA Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'middle-east-considerations', text: 'Middle East Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'UAE Insurance Guide', href: '/insurance-for/expats' },
  { title: 'Dubai Expat Guide', href: '/insurance-for/expats' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Middle East Network', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', axa: 'Very Good' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', axa: '€3M' },
  { feature: 'UAE Compliant', cigna: 'Yes', bupa: 'Yes', axa: 'Yes' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing Dubai', cigna: 'Extensive', bupa: 'Extensive', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Saudi Arabia', cigna: 'Very Good', bupa: 'Good', axa: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Qatar Network', cigna: 'Good', bupa: 'Very Good', axa: 'Good' },
  { feature: 'Arabic Support', cigna: 'Yes', bupa: 'Yes', axa: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Best For', cigna: 'Overall choice', bupa: 'Premium service', axa: 'Value seekers' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 35', cigna: '$350-550/mo', bupa: '$380-600/mo', axa: '$280-420/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', cigna: '$500-750/mo', bupa: '$550-800/mo', axa: '$400-580/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 40', cigna: '$800-1,200/mo', bupa: '$900-1,300/mo', axa: '$650-950/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', cigna: '$1,100-1,700/mo', bupa: '$1,200-1,800/mo', axa: '$900-1,350/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs AXA: Best Insurance for Middle East Expats 2026"
  description="Compare the top insurers for expats in the Middle East: Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and AXA Global. Coverage for UAE, Dubai, Saudi Arabia, Qatar, and more."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs AXA: Middle East Expat Insurance Compared"
  subheadline="Three premium insurers competing in the Gulf. All meet UAE requirements—here's how to choose between them."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <h2 id="quick-verdict">Quick Verdict</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-2 border-primary-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Overall</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Cigna Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Largest network in UAE and Saudi. Best app. Arabic support. Most corporate expats use Cigna.</p>
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-purple-50 border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Premium Service</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Bupa Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Excellent Dubai and Qatar networks. Premium customer service. Lifetime renewal guarantee.</p>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Best Value</p>
      <p class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">AXA Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">15-20% cheaper. UAE compliant. Good network in Dubai and Abu Dhabi. Solid value choice.</p>
      <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block w-full text-center bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white text-sm font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded transition-colors no-underline" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    The Middle East has world-class healthcare—but it's expensive. All three insurers are UAE-compliant and have strong Gulf networks. Cigna dominates the corporate expat market. Bupa offers premium service. AXA provides solid coverage at better prices.
  </p>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h2 id="cigna-global">Cigna Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Market Leader</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Network</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Arabic Support</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Cigna Global dominates the Middle East expat insurance market—most corporate relocations use them. The network is extensive across UAE, Saudi Arabia, and Qatar, with the best direct billing relationships at premium hospitals. Arabic-speaking support available 24/7.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Largest provider network in the Gulf</li>
    <li>Best direct billing at Cleveland Clinic Abu Dhabi, Mediclinic, etc.</li>
    <li>24/7 Arabic-speaking customer service</li>
    <li>UAE DHA/HAAD compliant</li>
    <li>Best app for the region</li>
    <li>Strong Saudi Arabia presence</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Premium pricing may exceed what's needed</li>
    <li>Some smaller emirates have limited direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Corporate expats in UAE or Saudi Arabia. Those who want the largest network and best service. Anyone who doesn't want to deal with reimbursement claims.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="bupa-global">Bupa Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Premium Service</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Qatar Strong</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Lifetime Renewal</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium service with excellent networks in Dubai and Qatar specifically. Their lifetime renewal guarantee means you can't be dropped for developing conditions—important in a region where you might stay long-term. Premium pricing, but premium service.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Excellent Dubai and Qatar networks</li>
    <li>Premium customer service</li>
    <li>Lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
    <li>Good pre-existing condition handling</li>
    <li>Arabic support available</li>
    <li>Strong at premium hospitals</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Most expensive option</li>
    <li>Saudi Arabia network smaller than Cigna</li>
    <li>App not as polished as Cigna</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Long-term Dubai or Qatar expats. Those who prioritize service over cost. Anyone wanting lifetime renewal protection.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <h2 id="axa-global">AXA Global</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Best Value</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">UAE Compliant</span>
    <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-xs font-medium rounded">Good Network</span>
  </div>

  <p>
    AXA Global offers UAE-compliant coverage at 15-20% less than Cigna and Bupa. The network is smaller but covers all major hospitals in Dubai and Abu Dhabi. A smart choice for cost-conscious expats who don't need the absolute largest network.
  </p>

  <p><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>15-20% cheaper than competitors</li>
    <li>UAE DHA/HAAD compliant</li>
    <li>Good network in Dubai, Abu Dhabi</li>
    <li>Comprehensive coverage included</li>
    <li>Strong mental health benefits</li>
    <li>Good for families</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Smaller direct billing network</li>
    <li>Limited Arabic support</li>
    <li>Saudi Arabia presence limited</li>
    <li>€3M limit vs unlimited</li>
    <li>More reimbursement claims needed</li>
  </ul>

  <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Cost-conscious UAE expats. Families looking for value. Those in Dubai or Abu Dhabi where AXA's network is strongest.</p>

  <div class="my-6">
    <a href="/go/axa-global" class="inline-block bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-medium py-2.5 px-5 rounded-lg transition-colors no-underline mr-3" style="color: white !important;">Get AXA Quote</a>
    <a href="/providers/axa-global" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 font-medium">Read Full Review →</a>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare All Three"
    description="Get personalized quotes from Cigna, Bupa, and AXA for your Middle East destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing Comparison</h2>

  <p>
    Middle East coverage costs more than most regions due to high healthcare costs in the Gulf. Dubai and Abu Dhabi are among the world's most expensive healthcare markets. Budget accordingly.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    *Estimated ranges for Middle East coverage including UAE. Prices vary based on age, health, specific emirate, and coverage options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="middle-east-considerations">Middle East Specific Considerations</h2>

  <h3>UAE Mandatory Insurance Requirements</h3>
  <p>
    The UAE requires all residents to have health insurance. Dubai (DHA) and Abu Dhabi (HAAD) have specific minimum requirements. All three insurers offer compliant plans, but verify your specific emirate's requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>United Arab Emirates</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Excellent—direct billing at Cleveland Clinic, Mediclinic, American Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Very good network, strong at premium hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Good coverage in Dubai and Abu Dhabi, more limited in other emirates</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Saudi Arabia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Best network—strong presence in Riyadh, Jeddah, Dammam</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Good but smaller network than Cigna</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Limited presence—may need more reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Qatar</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna:</strong> Good network at major hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa:</strong> Strong presence—good at Sidra, HMC facilities</li>
    <li><strong>AXA:</strong> Adequate coverage, some direct billing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Healthcare Costs in the Gulf</h3>
  <p>
    The Middle East has excellent private healthcare, but costs are high. A hospital stay can easily exceed $1,000/day. Unlimited coverage (Cigna, Bupa) provides peace of mind. AXA's €3M limit is usually sufficient but could be tested by a serious illness.
  </p>

  <h2 id="best-for">Which Is Best For You?</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want the largest network in the region</li>
        <li>Live in UAE or Saudi Arabia</li>
        <li>Prefer Arabic-speaking support</li>
        <li>Want the best app experience</li>
        <li>Prefer direct billing over reimbursement</li>
        <li>Are on a corporate expat package</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Live in Dubai or Qatar specifically</li>
        <li>Want lifetime renewal guarantee</li>
        <li>Prioritize premium customer service</li>
        <li>Plan to stay in the region long-term</li>
        <li>Have pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>Value service over cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-5">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Choose AXA Global if you...</h3>
      <ul class="text-neutral-600 space-y-1">
        <li>Want to save 15-20% on premiums</li>
        <li>Live in Dubai or Abu Dhabi</li>
        <li>Are comfortable with some reimbursement claims</li>
        <li>Have a family and need to manage costs</li>
        <li>Don't need unlimited coverage</li>
        <li>Value mental health benefits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is international insurance required in the UAE?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. UAE law requires all residents to have health insurance. Your visa sponsor (employer or self) must provide compliant coverage. All three insurers offer UAE-compliant plans that meet DHA (Dubai) and HAAD (Abu Dhabi) requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use local UAE insurance instead?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, but local plans only cover you in the UAE. If you travel frequently or might need treatment elsewhere, international insurance provides global coverage. Many expats choose international for the flexibility.
  </p>

  <h3>Which insurer is best for Saudi Arabia?</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna has the strongest Saudi network, followed by Bupa. AXA has limited presence. If you're primarily in Saudi Arabia, Cigna is the safest choice for direct billing and provider access.
  </p>

  <h3>Do I need unlimited coverage in the Middle East?</h3>
  <p>
    Gulf healthcare is expensive, but €3M (AXA's limit) covers most scenarios. Unlimited (Cigna, Bupa) provides extra peace of mind. If you have chronic conditions or anticipate complex care, unlimited is safer.
  </p>

  <h3>What about coverage during Ramadan?</h3>
  <p>
    Healthcare operates normally during Ramadan, though some facilities have modified hours. Emergency care is always available. Your insurance coverage is unaffected by religious observances.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. UAE and other Gulf countries have specific insurance requirements that change. Verify compliance with your specific emirate and employer requirements.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
